SCREENSHOT: 02-fake-token.png
=================================
HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized
X-Powered-By: Express
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8

Request: GET /api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer thisisnotreal

Response:
{
  "message": "Invalid or expired token."
}

Status: 401 Unauthorized
Expected: 401 Unauthorized ✅ PASS

The middleware correctly rejects an invalid token by:
1. Attempting to verify the malformed token
2. Catching the jwt.verify() error in the catch block
3. Returning 401 with error message (never calling next())
